		Comment <a href="#c_1713665321">10</a> by Russ Johnson
		posted on 5/17/2007 at 7:39 PM
		</div>
		<div class="comment_text"><p>@Ray</p><p>I know price is not the only concern but look at all the areas that are eventually affected by price. Ultimately the price drives out opensource development. I know RIAForge has done GREAT things to improve upon this but I feel like the lack of opensource options even further push new developers away from CF.</p><p>Development time is still sort of relevant to this discussion but when you combine it with the lack of opensource applications, theres no comparison. Granted we all know you can code a comparable app is CF in less time than you can in PHP but when I can use a free CMS and a free shopping cart system written in PHP that are full-featured apps and only need to skin them for a client, I just saved a BUNCH of time (and money). This again is affected by price.</p><p>Dont get me wrong. I have been coding CF for 10 years now and I LOVE it and have no plans to move away from it, BUT I think things need to change a bit to help grow the programmer base and get new users into CF. In my opinion, its the cost that is killing CF in the battle against languages like PHP and Ruby.</p><p>Hopefully Railo and Smith will help to solve that in the near future.</p></div>
	</div>
</div>
		
